|stock_os=Linux;2.4.31 |tp_firmware=OpenWrt, |802dot11_protocols=bg |default_ssid=@HomeXXXX |default_ssid_regex=^@Home[0-9A-F]{4}$ |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |oui=00:1E:E5, 00:21:29, 00:22:6B |oui_eth=00:1E:E5, 00:21:29, 00:22:6B }} ''Wireless-G Broadband Router with 2 Phone Ports''
{{SupportPage|vendor=Linksys|model=WRTU54G-TM}} 2010-12-16 final firmware version 1.00.25 WRTU54G-TM serial numbers appear to start with '''QMF0'''. {{TechInfoDepot|Linksys_WRTU54G-TM_v1.0}} (board images) [http://wiki.scottn.us/wrtu54g-tm WRTU54G-TM and OpenWrt] :[http://wiki.scottn.us/wrtu54g-tm:info Info dump] "613-180173R" is silkscreened on the board. :This is presumed to be a '''Tecom''' P/N. The default SSID is '''@HomeXXXX''' where '''XXXX''' is the last two octets of the wireless interface MAC address (upper case letters). The power adapter included with the device is a PSA18R-120P (12V, 1.5A). ==Images== File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM angled front.jpg|angled, front File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM angled back.jpg|angled, back File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM front side.jpg|front (LED) side File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM opp label side.jpg|opposite label side File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM top side.jpg|top side File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM port side.jpg|port side File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM label side.jpg|label side File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM label1.jpg|label1 File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM label2.jpg|label2 File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM power adapter.jpg|power adapter [[Has images::external| ]][[Has images::label| ]][[Has images::power adapter| ]] File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM board top.jpg|board top File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM Switch.jpg|Switch File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM board ID.jpg|board ID File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM phone chips.jpg|phone chips File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM board bot.jpg|board bottom File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM ADM8668FX.jpg|ADM8668FX CPU File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM Flash.jpg|Flash File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM RAM.jpg|RAM File:Linksys WRTU54G-TM RT2561S.jpg|Ralink WiMAC/BB ===Serial=== ====Pinout====
